<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Current implementation of the rewrite router does not allow passing array parameters in the /{key}/{value} structure. This prevents creating nicely structured URL's from dynamic data.</p>

<p>Passing arrays can be easily implemented by changing line 174 in Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Module, from:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$params[$key] = $val;
</code></pre>

<p>To:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$params[$key] = (isset($params[$key]) ? (array_merge((array) $params[$key],array($val))): $val);
</code></pre>

<p>Which would create an array when the same parameter key is declared multiple times. I wrote a short article about this issue and explained in greater detail on: [<a href="http://www.techfounder.net/2008/06/23/passing-arrays-to-zend_controller_router/">http://techfounder.net/2008/06/â€¦</a>]</p>

